en_132218_0	According to scientists in Brazil the mosquito-borne Zika virus may be even more dangerous than previously thought.
en_132218_1	The scientists told the BBC that Zika could be behind more damaging neurological conditions, affecting the babies of up to a fifth of infected pregnant women.
en_132218_2	Rates of increase in Zika infection in some parts of Brazil have slowed, thanks to better information about preventing the disease.
en_132218_3	But the search for a vaccine is still in the early stages.
